come with me. I want to see where the goblin
hunter rises in the marsh, and to hear about
the fairishes, as you call them--but, make
haste! What's the matter? Get my horse, I
say."

"l'll see thee damned, before I be thy ser-
vant!" growled the lad.

"You'll see me me what?" asked Catherine
in surprise.

"Damned--thou saucy witch!" he replied.

"There, Miss Cathy! you see you have got
into pretty company,"I interposed. "Nice words
to be used to a young lady I Pray don't begin
to dispute with him--Come, let us seek for
Minny ourselves, and begone."

"But Ellen," cried she, staring, fixed in
astonishment. "How dare he speak so to me?
Mustn't he be made to do as I ask him? You
wicked creature, I shall tell papa what you said
--Now then!"

Hareton did not appear to feel this threat;
so the tears sprung into her eyes with indig-
